4 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
5 Sec. 1. CHARTER AMENDMENT APPROVAL
6 The General Assembly approves the amendment to the charter of the City
7 of Burlington as set forth in this act. Voters approved the proposal of
8 amendment on March 4, 2025.
9 Sec. 2. 24 App. V.S.A. chapter 3 is amended to read:
10 CHAPTER 3. CITY OF BURLINGTON
11 * * *
12 § 510. BAN ON FIREARMS IN PREMISES LICENSED TO SERVE
13 ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES
14 (a) Statutes superseded. This section expressly supersedes 24 V.S.A. §§
15 2291(8) and 2295 and authorizes the City to regulate the possession and
16 carrying of firearms pursuant to this section.
17 (b) Ban. Within the City of Burlington, no person may knowingly possess
18 a firearm, as defined by 13 V.S.A. § 4016(a)(3), in any premises licensed to
19 serve alcoholic beverages.
20 (c) Exceptions. This provision shall not apply to:
